SIMPLE: puffy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Puffy
<hw>Puff"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Swelled
with air, or any soft matter; tumid with a soft substance; bloated;
fleshy; <as>as, a <ex>puffy</ex> tumor</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ A very stout,
<xex>puffy</xex> man.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Thackeray.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Hence, inflated; bombastic; <as>as, a <ex>puffy</ex>
style</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pug</ent>⟦br⟧
